President Joe Biden and Amir Tamim bin Hamad Al Thani of Qatar recently had a conversation to reaffirm the strong friendship between the United States and Qatar. President Biden expressed gratitude for Qatar's generous support in evacuating U.S. citizens, diplomatic staff, partner nations, and vulnerable Afghan nationals from Afghanistan. He acknowledged that this evacuation is the largest airlift in history and credited Qatar's early assistance in facilitating the transfer of thousands of people daily. The President also thanked the Amir for Qatar's longstanding role in facilitating intra-Afghanistan talks. Both leaders emphasized the need for continued close coordination on developments in Afghanistan and the wider Middle East. They also welcomed an upcoming summit of regional states to be held in Baghdad later this month.